Cette page est aussi disponible en français: Français:CatégorieOutilsDuProgrammeur

Click the heading title to list all pages with information
related to utilities for programming.  

This is an attempt to collect tools that help programmers be more
productive in dealing with programs written in languages such as C,
C++, or Java.  

'''For EmacsLisp coding support, see 
CategoryCode.'''  More general Emacs programming
information is at CategoryProgramming. Debugging tools are listed in CategoryDebug.

If you are looking for an interface to some external utility not
directly related to programming, see CategoryExternalUtilities
instead.

See also CategoryVersionControl.

Compiling:

* AntCall -- run ant from a buffer
* CompilationMode
* CompileCommand -- cutomizations to the `compile-command' variable
** UsingMakefileFromParentDirectory
* CompileInsideScratchbox run emacs outside, but compile inside scratchbox
** CreatingYourOwnCompileErrorRegexp
** Lisp:compile-.el and Lisp:compile+.el -- enhancements to <code>compile.el</code>.
* FlyMake -- runs make on the fly, highlights errors/warnings in source buffer
* ModeCompile -- another better `compile'
* SmartCompile -- a better `compile'

Interpreted files:
* MakingScriptsExecutableOnSave

Documenting code:

* ArScanner -- help free software developers to manage author rights and licenses
* DoxyMacs -- a documentation system for C and C++
* JavadocHelp -- Search a Java class through multiple online and local javadocs
* JdeDocIndex -- Native Javadoc integration for the Emacs JDE
* SemanticRecoder -- Includes a smart comment writer, and texinfo code generation.
* TexiDoclet -- generate Java documentation in Info format

Code navigation and hints:

* CScopeAndEmacs -- quickly look up where a symbol is defined, where it is called, and so on
* EevMode -- EmacsLisp hyperlinks helps us navigate source codes.
* Emacs tags -- record and locate identifier definitions in source files based on a [[tags file]]
** overview: EmacsTags (etags)
** building tags files
*** BuildTags -- more information on how to create these files
*** ExuberantCtags (ctags) -- supports more languages and editors than etags
** navigating to tags (definitions)
*** [[Icicles - Tags Enhancements]] -- find or browse tags from all tags files (including multiple matches for a tag)
*** EtagsSelect -- select from multiple matches to a tag
*** EctagsSelect -- an etags replacement that uses ExuberantCtags and eldoc to good effect
*** EtagsStack -- Navigate the tags stack
*** EtagsTable -- Set the tags-table-list based on the current file
* GnuGlobal -- database of code identifiers and tags
* GonzuiForEmacs -- emacs interface of gonzui, a source code search engine.
* IdeBridge -- code completion, refactoring, compilation for C# (only available on win32 now).
* IdUtils -- database of code identifiers
* ImenuMode -- move quickly among definitions of functions, macros, classes, types, whatever
** [[Icicles - Other Search Commands#IciclesImenu|Icicles Imenu]] -- Imenu with regexp [[Completion]], and, like EmacsTags, works across multiple buffers, files, and saved regions
* SimpleCallTree -- returns a call-tree data structure saying which function calls which function using Emacs's font highlighting of functions
* XreFactory -- proprietary tool which claims to provide code completion, source browsing and refactoring.

File changes:

* DiffMode -- inspect, edit and apply diffs
* EdiffMode -- interactively diffs, merges and patches.
* EdiffTrees -- recursively uses EdiffMode for two variants of a directory tree
* EdiffUrl -- comparing buffer to a web url.
* EmergeDiff -- graphical interface to "diff"

[:ProjectSupport]
Projects (code) -- creating and managing:

* CollectionOfEmacsDevelopmentEnvironmentTools (CEDET)
* DiredMode -- operate on project files
** [[GrepMode#GrepOnlyMarkedFiles|grep only marked files in Dired]] -- search project files
* [[ELPA]]
* EmacsCodeBrowser (ECB)
* [[eproject]] - project workspaces for emacs
* EtaskMode
* FindFileInProject
* [[Icicles - Support for Projects]]
* IdeSkel
* JavaDevelopmentEnvironment
* [http://www.littleredbat.net/mk/code/mk-project.html mk-project] --  Quickly switch between projects and perform operations on a per-project basis
* MultiTerm
* [[Profiles]] - Non-invasive user settings common to multiple projects
* ProjectBufferMode -- generic mode to handle projects
* ProjectLocalVariables
* [http://www.shellarchive.co.uk/content/lisp/project-root.el project-root.el]
* ProjectSettings
* ProjectWizard
* ProjmanMode
* SimpleProjectManagment
* SrSpeedbar
* [http://www.ozymandias.dk/emacs/emacs.html#vps vps] Projects as directory sets (by VagnJohansen)

Package management and installers:

* PortageMode -- Search and install Gentoo packages -- Also see EmacsForGentoo
* RpmSpecMode -- Edit SPEC files for building RPMs.
* WajigMode -- An interface for wajig

Related tools and information:

* AsciiMode -- displays ASCII code
* AsciiTable and EbcdicTable -- Display charts of characters and their codes for reference purposes.
* CodeBeautifying -- reindents code and rewraps comments.
* ConnectedGraphEditor (COGRE) -- a base library for editing and manipulating connected graphs
* EmacsPmd - Java source code analyzer
* GprofMode - Add hyperlinks to output files of the GNU profiler
* PopupRuler -- Measure strings report layouts etc. in source files.
* PrettyLambda -- a way to use a lambda character in scheme-mode
* RemoteProgramDevelopment -- editing and running code on a remote host
* Lisp:vhdl-goto-def.el and Lisp:vhdl-process-wave.el -- some stuff for vhdl coders.

